column5: ok i may have made the fish a little bigger  a flooded capitol hill didn't give it away?
Yeah, but I wanted to be nerdy. =P

Fishing right off the CN tower is as urban as it gets. Best pike fishing  i ever experienced right here in Toronto. Got my PB pike here of 43".  Have posted reports way back when i caught these with buddy Dude...      Even caught some largies down here.    Caught this pike in May 2007 turns out to be last time i was there.   Caught these in Toronto harbourfront eh.

Caught this bad boy in the dirty Shwa last fall, about 10 minutes from home.       This guy came down in Pickering by the Nuke plant (and no it wasn't glowing green.....)         This guy came out from Caeseria last year       I was hoping to have a bass or 2 to post from Port Perry, but I have not managed to get out yet this season, damned renovations are really cramping my fishing time!!!    Daryl

27 incher from Toronto this year:    Plus all the other toronto pike from my reports. I was out fishing this year for the first time for pike in Toronto and was amazed.  I had also caught a lot of crappie and a tiny oos largemouth but forgot to put my sd card back in my camera, but I'm heading down there today in hopes of catching a bass.
